            {/* Important Notes */}
            <div className="mt-6 p-4 bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg">
              <h4 className="font-semibold text-yellow-800 mb-2">âš ï¸ Important Notes:</h4>
                             <ul className="text-yellow-700 text-sm space-y-1">
                 <li>â€¢ Always start with lower concentrations and increase gradually</li>
                 <li>â€¢ Monitor your plants for signs of nutrient burn or deficiency</li>
                 <li>â€¢ PPM/EC levels: Veg 800-1200, Flower 1200-1600</li>
                 <li>â€¢ pH ranges: Hydro/Coco/Soilless 5.5-6.5, Soil 6.0-7.0</li>
                 <li>â€¢ Hard water (Winnipeg): CalMag not needed, may cause lockout</li>
                 <li>â€¢ Soft/RO water: CalMag essential to replace missing minerals</li>
                 <li>â€¢ Dry nutrients (Jack's, MegaCrop): Mix slowly to prevent clumping</li>
                 <li>â€¢ Advanced Nutrients pH Perfect: Minimal pH adjustment needed</li>
                 <li>â€¢ Change nutrient solution every 7-14 days</li>
               </ul>
            </div>
          </div>


        </div>
